 "name": "Wilderness Evasion and Pursuit",
 "system": "openfrp74",
 "category": "combat-rules",
 "description": "Castle folk pursue on 1-3 hostile, 1 neutral. Evasion odds run from 90% (tiny party, monsters few) to 05% (great party, monsters many) per the table; party surprise doubles them, monster surprise voids them but for magic or woods (+25%, and 10% even surprised); double speed shifts them 25% either way. Pursuit moves in a random direction each hex; a faster monster catches on 50% each hex (woods or swamp −25%), until escape or melee. Each pursuit hex costs half a day's rest after, wandering monsters checked with two dice on rest days.",
